3 amending the 3rd blocked paragraph to read:
4 Notwithstanding this subsection, the bureau may select a person or persons to perform
5 professional, architectural or engineering services from the list described in this subsection
6 without advertising or competitive selection if the cost of the services does not exceed
7 $25,000 $50,000. The bureau shall solicit names for placement on a list by placing a
8 general advertisement for professional, architectural or engineering services in newspapers
9 that taken together have general circulation throughout the State. The bureau may
10 substitute advertisement in professional journals or other publications that it finds equally
11 effective in reaching the intended audience. The bureau may require persons responding
12 to the advertisement to complete a qualifying questionnaire designed to address experience
13 and expertise in performing the type of work advertised. The bureau shall prepare a list of
14 respondents that it determines qualified and update the list at least every 2 years.
15 SUMMARY
1166 This bill amends the informal bidding process for the selection of professional,
1177 architect and engineer services by the Department of Administrative and Financial
1188 Services, Bureau of General Services through the use of a list of qualified service providers
1199 by increasing the cost of services limit from $25,000 to $50,000.
